    • Method Detail

      • getPathsToDelete

        public Set<Path> getPathsToDelete()
        Deprecated. 
        Description copied from interface: DatasetVersion
        Get set of Path that should be deleted to delete this dataset version.

        Each path will be deleted recursively, and the deletions will be done serially. As such, this set should be the minimal set of Path that can be deleted to remove the dataset version. (For example, the parent directory of the files in the dataset, assuming all descendants of that directory are files for this dataset version).

        Returns:
        Minimal set of Path to delete in order to remove the dataset version.
